With her math levels, can she even count that far?

80
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:24,440
   

81
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,760
Sorry, everyone!

82
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,350
We're all out of bubble tea for today.

83
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,030
Come earlier tomorrow!

84
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:30,440
So sorry about this.

85
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:33,030
So sorry! So sorry!

86
00:04:33,030 --> 00:04:34,590
We waited forever... Let's go.

87
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:36,320
Sorry!

88
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:37,640
Hold on, Tiantian!

89
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,010
We've been waiting forever, too!

90
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:42,790
Don't worry!

91
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:45,750
Of course, I've saved some for my friends!

92
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:48,960
   

93
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:51,539
Crazy Good Bubble Tea, here we come!

94
00:04:51,539 --> 00:04:54,150
One per person! No exceptions.

95
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:57,440
A bucket-sized cup!

96
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:59,440
Anything for my girl Xuejiao!

97
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,840
Consider this my friendship discount.

98
00:05:04,135 --> 00:05:06,150
Is it good?

99
00:05:06,150 --> 00:05:07,520
- Awesome! 
 - It's good, right?

100
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:09,560
Girl, if you sold this off-campus,

101
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,690
you'd crush every bubble tea shop out there.

102
00:05:11,690 --> 00:05:13,030
No kidding.

103
00:05:13,030 --> 00:05:16,230
Today, some guy in line said he's an investor

104
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:17,998
and wants to invest in me.

105
00:05:17,998 --> 00:05:20,528
That's great! What did you say?

106
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:28,090
He said he was choosing between me and a shop called "HiTea" shop...

107
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:32,320
But he really liked mine.

108
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:34,960
So, what did you say?

109
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,560
I answered him very directly.

110
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:39,470
I told him, if you want milk tea, you're welcome here.

111
00:05:39,470 --> 00:05:41,230
If you are trying to scam me, dream on.

112
00:05:41,230 --> 00:05:42,640
There are so many scammers out there.

113
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:45,720
Like I'm going to fall for that! You have to be kidding.

114
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:53,880
Thanks to what I learned from your drunk kiss disaster; I appreciate it!

115
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:56,360
Totally, right?

116
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,240
Right?  There are so many con artists these days.

117
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:04,010
My goodness.

118
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:05,060
Let me say, Sister,

119
00:06:05,060 --> 00:06:07,860
we're way too sharp for that nonsense.

120
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:11,881
 With 90% of the votes in, the results show... 

121
00:06:11,881 --> 00:06:13,897
 I wonder what Xuejiao's doing. 

122
00:06:13,897 --> 00:06:15,810
 What's on her mind? 

123
00:06:15,810 --> 00:06:19,010
 Maybe she's remembering what she said? 

124
00:06:19,010 --> 00:06:22,430
 In her previous life, I was her boss, and she hated me. 

125
00:06:22,430 --> 00:06:26,860
 This time, I'm the senior she looks up to. 

126
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:30,398
 So, I'll stay in this role to get along with her. 

127
00:06:30,398 --> 00:06:34,078
 It's better this way, for both of us. 

128
00:06:35,870 --> 00:06:38,560
   

129
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:41,490
   

130
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:48,370
 Ever since Senior Brother Lin left, the lab's felt too quiet. 

131
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:50,540
 I wonder what he's doing now. 

132
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:53,370
 Is his work going well? 

133
00:06:53,370 --> 00:06:55,310
 We barely talk anymore. 

134
00:06:55,310 --> 00:06:58,740
 He keeps his distance, too. 

135
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:00,080
 Grown-ups, you know. 

136
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:02,620
 We move on. 

137
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:06,760
 Whatever happened that farewell night 

138
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:08,870
 has gone with the wind. 

139
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,500
Is this the attitude you want to have

140
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,950
as part of the Jinghai University lab?

141
00:07:18,811 --> 00:07:20,541
You...

142
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:22,580
What's going on?

143
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:26,290
Lin Zhihua, what's going on?

144
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:31,400
Why are you guys back so soon?

145
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:34,090
Did the B&amp;C Motors deal fall apart?

146
00:07:37,538 --> 00:07:40,003
Actually,

147
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:42,978
quite the opposite.

148
00:07:42,978 --> 00:07:46,260
This trip to Germany wasn't about securing an offer.

149
00:07:46,260 --> 00:07:50,161
We wanted B&amp;C Motors to invest in our C1 project.

150
00:07:50,161 --> 00:07:52,862
At first, they acted all high and mighty, saying there was no precedent.

151
00:07:52,862 --> 00:07:54,930
Now they've compromised.

152
00:07:54,930 --> 00:07:59,321
I'm telling you, kid, that was a huge gamble.

153
00:07:59,321 --> 00:08:00,532
What if they didn't agree?

154
00:08:00,532 --> 00:08:04,895
Professor Tan, Old Lin went all in this time, and it paid off.

155
00:08:04,895 --> 00:08:07,960
Even I was almost fooled.

156
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:10,870
Honestly, I never wanted to work for them.

157
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:12,400
Even if it didn't work out,

158
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:15,839
we had funding from Junlian and Director Zhao as backup.

159
00:08:15,839 --> 00:08:18,640
Now B&amp;C is feeling the heat, and they're scrambling.

160
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:22,420
They caved in on a bunch of our terms.

161
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:25,040
We don't need to go overseas to work for them.

162
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:30,290
We can stay right here and build our own startup team here in China.

163
00:08:32,190 --> 00:08:34,640
You always take the riskiest path!

164
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:36,670
Feint east, strike west, you fool everyone!

165
00:08:36,670 --> 00:08:40,279
Even pulled off that crowd-funded farewell party?

166
00:08:40,279 --> 00:08:42,010
Once B&amp;C Motors' funding arrives,

167
00:08:42,010 --> 00:08:43,281
we'll pay it back ten times over.

168
00:08:43,281 --> 00:08:44,376
Is ten times enough?

169
00:08:44,376 --> 00:08:46,291
You have to leave the school with a decent investment share.

170
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,172
Don't worry, Professor Tan.

171
00:08:48,172 --> 00:08:50,983
I'll stay on to lead the lab.

172
00:08:50,983 --> 00:08:54,420
But besides the original C1 crew,

173
00:08:54,420 --> 00:08:56,570
I'll need an assistant.

174
00:08:56,570 --> 00:08:58,160
An assistant?

175
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,790
Professor Tan! How about me?

176
00:08:59,790 --> 00:09:01,000
Professor, I can do it!

177
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,610
- Professor, I'm your guy! 
 - All of you, shut up!

178
00:09:04,336 --> 00:09:08,387
More excited to work for Xiao Lin than for me, huh?

179
00:09:08,387 --> 00:09:09,340
   

180
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:11,950
- Grandmaster... 
 - Get back to work.

181
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:13,590
I've already got someone in mind.

182
00:09:13,590 --> 00:09:15,190
What?

183
00:09:18,121 --> 00:09:19,206
I'm just a freshman!

184
00:09:19,206 --> 00:09:20,420
How can I be your assistant?

185
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:23,990
You're the only one besides me who cracked Professor Tan's virus code.

186
00:09:23,990 --> 00:09:26,000
Who else could it be?

187
00:09:28,950 --> 00:09:30,480
Okay, fine.

188
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,590
Give me something to do.

189
00:09:39,310 --> 00:09:42,330
Gao Rui and I just wrapped up the C1 code.

190
00:09:42,330 --> 00:09:44,340
We need you to proofread it.

191
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,870
- How many lines? 
 - Over 10,000.

192
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,900
Are you and Senior Gao even human?

193
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:56,140
You just need to be efficient.

194
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,480
Your face is bad news, day or night.

195
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:02,250
What was that?

196
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,100
Nothing.

197
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:16,160
You sure you don't remember anything from the day we saw you off?

198
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:18,031
I do.

199
00:10:18,031 --> 00:10:21,512
- You didn't want me to leave and... 
 - Stop!

200
00:10:21,512 --> 00:10:24,480
Right now, I officially deny everything from that night.

201
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:26,910
Pure drunk talk.

202
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,070
Anyway, once you're done proofreading,

203
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:32,040
load it into the simulator.

204
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,960
We're testing tomorrow.

205
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:39,193
Got it. I'll go and get an external drive.

206
00:10:39,193 --> 00:10:40,973
No need.

207
00:10:41,940 --> 00:10:43,850
Use this.

208
00:10:51,540 --> 00:10:54,640
 Old Lin, since I was Xuejiao's first tutor, 

209
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:57,060
 that makes me your senior. Right? 

210
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,790
 Got any tips for me? 

211
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:02,300
 She's not interested in you. 

212
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,830
 If she were really into you, 

213
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:08,520
 how could she drop this drive off and leave without a word? 

214
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:22,660
Thanks.

215
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:36,140
   

216
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:58,660
Senior Brother Lin, maybe you should get back to work?

217
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:01,500
I can't concentrate with you staring like that.

218
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:06,240
My assistant is really bold.

219
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,950
I'm leaving.

220
00:12:27,070 --> 00:12:30,140
So this is the project you dragged me here to check out?

221
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:33,450
I have to say, Jinghai University's got some serious talent.

222
00:12:33,450 --> 00:12:36,290
Even the cafeteria's bubble tea went viral.

223
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:40,300
Crazy Good Bubble Tea.

224
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:41,970
What kind of name is that?

225
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:46,360
It could be rebranded to "Tiantian's Tea".

226
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,820
Tiantian's Tea?

227
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:53,260
   

228
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:56,135
- Isn't that... 
 - That's right.

229
00:12:56,135 --> 00:13:00,490
It is Gu Xuejiao's high school friend, Sun Tiantian.

230
00:13:00,490 --> 00:13:03,670
Such a clever play on words. 
  ("Tian" is a homophone for sweet) 

231
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,520
What's the deal?

232
00:13:10,950 --> 00:13:13,800
So, a while back, I got this email.

233
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:19,190
It's this proposal. 
    

234
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:21,640
I loved it the moment I read it.

235
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:25,000
   

236
00:13:38,940 --> 00:13:41,040
So, are you going to invest?

237
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:43,020
Highly likely.

238
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,890
But when I visited just now,

239
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:49,260
the girl running it didn't seem all that sharp.

240
00:13:49,260 --> 00:13:52,120
Now I'm not so sure.

241
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:54,660
Who do you think sent me that proposal?

242
00:13:54,660 --> 00:13:57,380
Could someone be trying to scam me?

243
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:59,430
No way. I have to get to the bottom of this.

244
00:13:59,430 --> 00:14:01,440
Hey, don't be so hasty.

245
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:04,810
Let's do this. Forward me the sender's email.

246
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:06,980
I'll handle it.

247
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:08,810
Finally acting like a grown-up

248
00:14:08,810 --> 00:14:11,400
and looking out for your big sis. Right?

249
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:17,610
See, this proposal is so detailed and exactly right about Gen Z consumer preferences.

250
00:14:17,610 --> 00:14:21,070
Not just that, it even forecasts upcoming market trends.

251
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:25,310
My own research team wouldn't dare to be this confident.

252
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:30,660
Honestly, I started wondering if the writer's a time traveler.

253
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:34,900
We're educated, don't go full sci-fi.

254
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,330
You don't get it.

255
00:14:36,330 --> 00:14:40,990
A good investor has to consider every possibility.

256
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,252
But, Sister, start saying "time travel" around Jinghai University

257
00:14:44,252 --> 00:14:46,750
and they'll think you're crazy.

258
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:52,860
Well, I guess my reputation is more important after all.

259
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,570
How have you been lately?

260
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:02,430
Do you want to give me an update on what's going on with you?

261
00:15:02,430 --> 00:15:04,370
I'm good.

262
00:15:06,190 --> 00:15:08,040
Something's bothering you.

263
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,380
You can tell?

264
00:15:11,380 --> 00:15:13,020
